            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-4437-glibc",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-4437 medium vulnerability for glibc package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in glibc (the GNU C Library). When an application uses the `gethostbyaddr` or `gethostbyaddr_r` functions with a `nsswitch.conf` configuration that specifies glibc's DNS backend, a remote attacker can send a specially crafted DNS (Domain Name System) response. This crafted response can cause the application to incorrectly interpret a non-answer section of the DNS response as a valid answer, leading to potential misbehavior or incorrect information processing."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-4437",
