              "id": "CVE-2026-1485-glib2",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-1485 low vulnerability for glib2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in Glib's content type parsing logic. This buffer underflow vulnerability occurs because the length of a header line is stored in a signed integer, which can lead to integer wraparound for very large inputs. This results in pointer underflow and out-of-bounds memory access. Exploitation requires a local user to install or process a specially crafted treemagic file, which can lead to local denial of service or application instability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-1485",
              "help": {
