              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-5358 high vulnerability for glibc package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in the GNU C Library (glibc). The obsolete `nis_local_principal` function contains a buffer overflow vulnerability. A remote attacker could exploit this by spoofing a crafted response to a User Datagram Protocol (UDP) request. This could allow the attacker to overwrite static data in the requesting application, potentially leading to data corruption or a denial of service."
              },
